      "title": "Timing Chain Installation (Cont'd)",
      "steps": [
        {
          "step": 15,
          "text": "Install idler sprocket bolt.",
          "figure_ref": "fig1",
          "warnings": [],
          "notes": []
        },
        {
          "step": 16,
          "text": "Install camshaft, camshaft brackets and distributor bracket. Tighten camshaft bracket bolts gradually in three stages:\na) 2 N\u00b7m (0.2 kg-m, 1 ft-lb)\nb) 5.9 N\u00b7m (0.6 kg-m, 4 ft-lb)\nc) 9 - 12 N\u00b7m (0.9 - 1.2 kg-m, 6 - 9 ft-lb)\nIf any part of valve assembly or camshaft is replaced, check valve clearance according to the reference data. After completing assembly check valve clearance. Refer to \"Checking\" and \"Adjusting\" in \"VALVE CLEARANCE\".\nReference data for initial setting of valve clearance (Cold):\n  Intake: 0.30 mm (0.012 in)\n  Exhaust: 0.35 mm (0.014 in)",
          "figure_ref": "fig2",
          "warnings": [],
          "notes": [
            "If any part of valve assembly or camshaft is replaced, check valve clearance according to the reference data.",
            "After completing assembly check valve clearance. Refer to \"Checking\" and \"Adjusting\" in \"VALVE CLEARANCE\".",
            "Reference data for initial setting of valve clearance (Cold): Intake 0.30 mm (0.012 in), Exhaust 0.35 mm (0.014 in)"
          ]
        },
        {
          "step": 17,
          "text": "Assemble camshaft sprocket with chain.\n\u2022 Set timing chain by aligning mating marks with those of camshaft sprockets.\n\u2022 Make sure sprocket's mating marks face engine front.",
          "figure_ref": "fig3",
          "warnings": [],
          "notes": [
            "Set timing chain by aligning mating marks with those of camshaft sprockets.",
            "Make sure sprocket's mating marks face engine front."
          ]
        }
      ]
